    • allMotorPIDControl

      public void allMotorPIDControl​(int tickCount, double peakSpeed, double maxSpeed, double rampTime, boolean motorFLForward, boolean motorFRForward, boolean motorRLForward, boolean motorRRForward, double Kp, double Ki, double Kd)
      PID motor control program to ensure all four motors are synchronized
      Parameters:
      tickCount - : absolute value of target tickcount of motor
      peakSpeed - : peak speed of motor rotation in tick per second
      maxSpeed - : max speed of motor rotation in tick per second
      rampTime - : motor speed ramp up/down time in sec
      motorFLForward - : front left motor is forward
      motorFRForward - : front right motor is forward
      motorRLForward - : rear left motor is forward
      motorRRForward - : rear right motor is forward
      Kp - : coefficient Kp
      Ki - : coefficient Ki
      Kd - : coefficient Kd by Andrew Chiang on 1/28/2020
